title: GettingStarted

!! Introduction

The ''TW MCP'' plugin adds a [[Model Context Protocol|https://modelcontextprotocol.io/]] (MCP) server to TiddlyWiki. This lets AI assistants like Claude, Gemini, and others read, search, render, and modify your wiki content through a standardised interface.

!! Prerequisites

You need Node.js (v24+), TiddlyWiki (globally installed), and the `TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH` environment variable pointing to the tw-mcp plugin location. See [[MCP Installation]] for detailed setup instructions.

!! Quick Start

!!! 1. Start the MCP server

From your wiki directory run:

```
tiddlywiki . --mcp
```

This starts the MCP server in read/write mode using stdio transport.

; Common options
: `readonly` — disable all write operations
: `label=<name>` — identify this instance (e.g. `label=claude`)
: `listen` — also start an HTTP server so browser and MCP share the same wiki store

Examples:

This command starts an MCP server with access to the wiki directory with file access.

```
tiddlywiki . --mcp readonly
```

This command starts an MCP server ''and'' at TiddlyWiki server, which have access to the same wiki-store. So changes written to the store will be directly visible in the browser with the next poll (default 60s).

```
tiddlywiki . --mcp listen label=primary port=8080
```

!!! 2. Register with Claude CLI

Add a `.mcp.json` file to your wiki directory:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "tiddlywiki": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "tiddlywiki",
      "args": [".", "--mcp", "label=claude"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then start Claude Code from that directory. The MCP server will be available automatically.

!! Available Tools

!!! Read tools

|! Tool |! Description |
|`get_tiddler` |Fetch tiddler metadata or full content |
|`list_tiddlers` |Browse titles with namespace summaries |
|`run_filter` |Execute TiddlyWiki filter expressions |
|`render_tiddler` |Render a tiddler to plain text or HTML |
|`render_text` |Render arbitrary wikitext |
|`get_wiki_info` |Wiki metadata, plugins, tiddler counts |
|`inspect_tree` |Analyse widget tree structure |
|`inspect_pos` |Render with source position tracking |
|`inspect_scope` |Inspect variable scope at a position |
|`inspect_tw` |Navigate the internal `$tw` object |

!!! Write tools (disabled in readonly mode)

|! Tool |! Description |
|`put_tiddler` |Create or update a tiddler |
|`delete_tiddler` |Delete a tiddler |
|`upload_file` |Upload binary files (images, PDFs) |
|`save_wiki_folder` |Export wiki as folder structure |
|`build_wiki` |Render wiki as single HTML file |

